{
  "stem": "27390.4",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "When we opened the letter, it said that my brother and my-- and my mother should report to be evacuated and deported, should report to a assembly place, where they will be deported, because they were not working.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "When my mother got this letter, she sat down, and she wrote a very nice letter.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "She-- she could write a very good letter.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And in the morning, she got up, very early.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "She knew where Rumkowski travels to his office.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "He-- Jews were not allowed to use any mechanical transport in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Even he didn't-- wasn't allowed to use a car.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "He had to have a horse-driven carriage.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she went along the-- the route where his carriage would pass, and she threw the letter onto the carriage.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the horses, they-- they-- they-- they jumped.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was nearly killed that morning.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Anyway, she could see that his-- his secretary-- the man was sitting next to him-- picked up this letter.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "After a few days, I must say, we got a reply, from-- signed by Rumkowski, dictated by him and signed, that he's taken note of the letter.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he understands.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He-- that-- that-- my mother wrote that he promised he would look after our family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so he said, he can-- he will let one of the two that was going to be deported go free.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But one of them has to go, has to be deported.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So it was a choice between my mother and my younger brother.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we decided-- we-- they decided that night.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were sitting and talking about it and discussing it, who should go, my mother or my brother.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We decided that my younger brother should go.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
